R Notebook

# initial value
n = 10000
s = seq(0,1, length.out = n)
K = 6
rk = 0.5
# bk function
bk <- function(k){
  return(0.2 * (k - 1))
}

# basis function
basis_function <- function(s, bk, rk){
  return((1 - ((s - bk)^2) / (rk^2))^2 * (abs(s - bk) < rk))
}
# sample points
result = data.frame(matrix(rep(NA, n), ncol = n))
for (k in 1:K) {
  bk_value = bk(k)
  result = rbind(result, basis_function(s, bk_value, rk))
}
result = result[-1, ]
result
# plot
plot(x = s, y = result[1, ], xlim = c(0, 1), ylim = c(0, 1), col = 1, main = "basis function", xlab = "S", ylab = "f(s)", cex = 0.05)
for (k in 2:K) {
  lines(x = s, y = result[k, ], col = k)
}
legend("topright", legend = paste("k = ", 1:K), col = 1:K, lty = 1, cex = 0.8)
